## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of recent empirical studies specifically addressing the nuances of birth order effects on personality. Additionally, cultural and familial variations can influence personality development, making it challenging to generalize findings across different populations. The persistence of stereotypes in popular culture also complicates the interpretation of scientific data, as public perception may not align with empirical evidence.

